The paper deals with the complexity of Sum-of-Squares proofs, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves polynomial systems and their properties, which falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DS) and Linear Algebra (cs.LO). The paper also mentions common use-cases of the SoS algorithm, such as Max-CSP, Balanced Separator, Max-Clique, Max-Bisection, and Unit-Vector constraints, which are topics in Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Scientific Computing (cs.SD).
